title: Heather Mizeur
deleted: In 2009, Mizeur was appointed to the White House Task Force of State Legislators for Health Reform,<ref>{{cite web | title = House of Delegates: Heather Mizeur| url =  http://msa.maryland.gov/msa/mdmanual/06hse/html/msa14627.html}}</ref> where she advised the [[Obama administration]] on state best practices to be included in the Affordable Care Act.

title: Heather Mizeur
added: Mizeur married her wife, Deborah, in a private ceremony in 2005 on the [[Chesapeake Bay]]. They were legally married in California in 2008. They reside on a 34-acre organic farm in [[Chestertown, Maryland]].<ref>{{cite web|last1=Alexander|first1=Kate S.|title=In bid for governor, Mizeur hopes 'to blow doors off'|url=http://www.gazette.net/article/20140108/NEWS/140109406/0/in-bid-for-governor-mizeur-hopes-x2018-to-blow-doors-off-x2019&template=gazette|archive-url=https://archive.today/20150501144216/http://www.gazette.net/article/20140108/NEWS/140109406/0/in-bid-for-governor-mizeur-hopes-x2018-to-blow-doors-off-x2019&template=gazette|url-status=dead|archive-date=1 May 2015|publisher=Gazette.net|accessdate=1 May 2015}}</ref>
